  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "wwk52AE/572G+ZlIkBgiICJYSbw=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Incremental rollout plan for `RedundancyLevel`\n\nBaseline to preserve: commit `1e95c27` on `main`.\n\n1. Thread `redundancyLevel` option through `SwarmClient.uploadFile` and `uploadData`.\n2. Expose a single shared constant `COLLAB_OPS_REDUNDANCY = RedundancyLevel.MEDIUM`.\n3. Apply at `collab-ops-feed.ts:138` **only**. Rebuild. Run existing two-Bee setup end-to-end.\n4. Compare observed op apply-latency to the ~10s baseline.\n5. Verify `calculateRemainingSize(true, MEDIUM)` in stamp-utilization logs still shows headroom.\n6. **Decision gate:** if Awaiting\u2192joined fires within ~5s of accept AND op latency \u2264 baseline, commit.\n7. **Expand** to `lifecycle.ts:169` (drive-bundle) and the manifest feeds only after the first step is green.\n8. **Back off** to `OFF` for ops (keeping MEDIUM only for long-lived bundles) if stamp exhaustion warnings appear.\n9. **Rollback path:** revert the 2\u20133 line flag additions \u2014 no data-shape changes, no migration.\n\nThe experiment is explicitly reversible at every step; measure before expanding.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
    }
  },
